Socks proxy daemon with ssh

=== Installation ===

Just run ./install.sh script as superuser, modify /etc/default/do-socks.cfg for your needs.
For trubleshooting you can use following command

$ tail -f /var/log/do-socks.log

omit the $ sign.

=== Uninstall ===

You have to run ./install.sh script with "remove" parameter as following example

$ ./install.sh remove

beware that it will remove /etc/default/do-socks.cfg so make a backup if you need.

=== Configuration ===

PROXY_BIND_TO       Address that you want to bind your proxy on it
PROXY_PORT          Port number of PROXY_BIND_TO
PROXY_DOMAIN        Proxy'x address or domain name
PROXY_USER          Username that ssh uses to connect to PROXY_DOMAIN
PROXY_RETRY_AFTER   Number of seconds that do-socks waits after each failure
OPTIONS             Any kind of options that you want to pass to ssh (e.g. -vp8442)
